HEADWORD: Epitrope
<hw>E*pit"ro*pe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/ reference, arbitration, fr. <?/ to turn over, to give up, yield;
<grk>'epi`</grk> upon, over + <?/ to turn.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A figure by which permission is either seriously or ironically
granted to some one, to do what he proposes to do; <it>e. g.</it>,
⟦ldquo⟧He that is unjust, let him be unjust still.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epizeuxis</ent>⟦br⟧
